SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYWednesday 1 June S10 V1 Swallows FC, who were top of the table at Christmas 2020, begin their fight for top flight survival in the Premier Soccer League promotion-relegation playoffs as they host Cape Town All Stars in Atteridgeville today. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Belarus U21 vs Cyprus U21: Belarus U21 vs Cyprus U21: Belarus’ under-21s beat their Cypriot counterparts 1-0 away in March in the European U-21 Championships. This match is being played in Armenia.M2 Malaysia vs Hong Kong: A friendly international in Kuala Lumpur before both countries play in Asian Cup qualifiers.M3 Swallows FC vs Cape Town All Stars: Swallows have had to ceded home advantage because the pitch at Dobsonville Stadium is under repair. All Stars compete in their first PSL relegation-promotion series.M4 Kuwait vs Singapore: Kuwait and Singapore clash in a friendly in Abu Dhabi. Singapore won their last meetings which was their first success in eight clashes between the two countries.M5 Angola vs Central African Republic: The start of the 2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers. Both countries have failed to win in their past five internationals.M6 Libya vs Botswana: Both countries have a new coach as they kick off the Cup of Nations qualifiers. Libya have not played in the finals since 2010 and Botswana since 2012.M7 Poland vs Wales: First of the Nations League matches over the next fortnight as Wales use the game to prepare for their World Cup playoff against either Scotland or Ukraine next week.M8 Australia vs Jordan: Australia face the UAE in a World Cup playoff in Doha on June 7 and warm-up with a friendly in Qatar against Jordan.M9 Italy vs Argentina: The ‘Finalissima’ is at Wembley in London between the European champions and Copa America winners. Argentina have beaten Italy in their last three head-to-head clashes.M10 Scotland vs Ukraine: World Cup semi-final playoff is a one-off game in Glasgow with the winner going to Cardiff to meet Wales for a place in the final in Qatar in November. Suggested permutation: R2.00 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1